const MACBETH_EXTRACT_A = `MACBETH
The night is thick with whispers. Every shadow
Holds a shape that was not there before,
And every silence hides a voice that speaks
Of what I have become. I was a soldier,
Honoured and praised, who drew his sword for Scotland —
Now I draw it for myself alone,
And the blade that once shone bright with righteous purpose
Is dulled with guilty blood.

[Enter a Servant.]

SERVANT
My lord, the thanes have gathered in the hall.
They wait upon your pleasure.

MACBETH
                              Let them wait.
What are their faces? Do they smile or frown?
Is there a man among them who dares meet
My eye without a flinch? I'll know my enemies
By the way they hold their cups — a steady hand
Proclaims a steady heart, and he whose fingers
Tremble at the rim betrays a trembling conscience.

SERVANT
They seem in good spirits, my lord.

MACBETH
Good spirits. Ay. So did the smiling Duncan
Seem in good spirits on that final night
When we were all good friends and all was well,
And I — I was the serpent in the garden
That smiled and smiled and struck. Go tell them
I shall attend them presently. Be gone.

[Exit Servant.]

What feast is this where every guest may be
A murderer, and every toast a lie?
I have supped full with horrors, and yet still
Must sit at table with a painted smile
And play the gracious host while all around me
Daggers hide in cloaks and poison sleeps in wine.`

